  "prompt": "How can I watch YouTube videos on a VLC media player?",
  "response": "You can watch YouTube videos directly through VLC Media Player by streaming them from the internet. Below are detailed methods to help you achieve this. Please note that due to YouTube's frequent updates and changes to their streaming protocols, some methods might require adjustments or may not work at all times.\n\n---\n\n## **Method 1: Using VLC\u2019s \"Open Network Stream\" Feature**\n\nThis is the simplest method and often works without any additional steps.\n\n1. **Copy the YouTube Video URL:**\n   - Open your web browser and navigate to [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/).\n   - Find the video you want to watch.\n   - Copy the video's URL from the browser's address bar. It should look something like `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID`.\n\n2. **Open VLC Media Player:**\n   - If you don\u2019t have VLC installed, download it from the [official VLC website](https://www.videolan.org/vlc/) and install it.\n\n3. **Access \"Open Network Stream\":**\n   - Launch VLC.\n   - Click on the **\"Media\"** menu in the top-left corner.\n   - Select **\"Open Network Stream\u2026\"** (Alternatively, you can press `Ctrl + N` on Windows or `Cmd + N` on macOS).\n\n4. **Paste the YouTube URL:**\n   - In the **\"Network\"** tab, paste the YouTube video URL",
